WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:25.760
The Umbrella by Claire Harris

00:25.760 --> 00:27.680
It is raining.

00:27.680 --> 00:30.800
The sky is grey.

00:30.800 --> 00:34.040
Carla goes to the market.

00:34.040 --> 00:36.760
She looks at the Umbrella's.

00:36.760 --> 00:39.600
She likes a red Umbrella.

00:39.600 --> 00:42.000
It's very smart.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.520
It costs ten dollars.

00:45.520 --> 00:48.120
Carla is a student.

00:48.120 --> 00:51.560
She doesn't have much money.

00:51.560 --> 00:55.560
I can give you seven dollars for that Umbrella.

00:55.560 --> 00:57.760
OK, young lady.

00:57.760 --> 01:00.520
This is your lucky day.

01:00.520 --> 01:02.680
Give me seven dollars.

01:02.680 --> 01:07.120
The Umbrella is yours.

01:07.120 --> 01:09.720
This is my lucky day.

01:09.720 --> 01:11.960
Says Carla.

01:11.960 --> 01:16.080
She holds the red Umbrella above her head.

01:16.080 --> 01:20.520
The rain falls on the Umbrella.

01:20.520 --> 01:23.840
Carla goes to a cake shop.

01:23.840 --> 01:26.720
She wants to buy some cakes.

01:26.720 --> 01:30.640
Her little brother loves cakes.

01:30.640 --> 01:33.160
She goes into the shop.

01:33.160 --> 01:38.320
She leaves her red Umbrella near the door.

01:38.320 --> 01:41.920
It is quiet inside the shop.

01:41.920 --> 01:45.800
Carla chooses three small cakes.

01:45.800 --> 01:49.600
She talks to the shop assistant.

01:49.600 --> 01:52.840
A customer is leaving the shop.

01:52.840 --> 01:55.560
She is a young woman.

01:55.560 --> 01:59.880
She is holding a cake box.

01:59.880 --> 02:03.240
Carla is going to leave the shop.

02:03.240 --> 02:07.280
But where is her Umbrella?

02:07.280 --> 02:10.680
There is one Umbrella near the door.

02:10.680 --> 02:14.160
It is not a red Umbrella.

02:14.160 --> 02:18.120
It is not Carla's Umbrella.

02:18.120 --> 02:22.680
This Umbrella is old and black.

02:22.680 --> 02:26.120
It has a pattern of yellow ducks.

02:26.120 --> 02:28.560
It is not smart.

02:28.560 --> 02:30.080
Carla takes the Umbrella.

02:33.920 --> 02:38.000
This is not my lucky day.

02:38.000 --> 02:41.680
Carla walks to the town square.

02:41.680 --> 02:44.880
A young man speaks to her.

02:44.880 --> 02:47.360
Hello?

02:47.360 --> 02:49.120
He smiles.

02:49.120 --> 02:52.760
Carla does not know this young man.

02:52.760 --> 02:56.640
She walks away quickly.

02:56.640 --> 03:00.400
The young man is following Carla.

03:00.400 --> 03:04.120
She walks into a crowd of people.

03:04.120 --> 03:09.000
The young man follows the black and yellow Umbrella.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.520
Hello?

03:10.520 --> 03:12.640
Wait!

03:12.640 --> 03:15.160
Carla turns.

03:15.160 --> 03:18.080
She looks at the young man.

03:18.080 --> 03:19.960
She is angry.

03:19.960 --> 03:21.520
Go away.

03:21.520 --> 03:23.600
She says.

03:23.600 --> 03:26.320
The young man is sad.

03:26.320 --> 03:28.600
Marisa, I'm sorry.

03:28.600 --> 03:32.560
He says, I'm very late.

03:32.560 --> 03:34.440
I'm not Marisa.

03:34.440 --> 03:36.800
Carla shouts.

03:36.800 --> 03:41.440
You are not Marisa, says the young man.

03:41.440 --> 03:45.920
He points at the black Umbrella with yellow ducks.

03:45.920 --> 03:48.480
That's her Umbrella.

03:48.480 --> 03:49.840
Oh.

03:49.840 --> 03:51.840
Says Carla.

03:51.840 --> 03:54.880
Who is Marisa?

03:54.880 --> 03:59.320
I don't know Marisa, says the young man.

03:59.320 --> 04:02.160
I'm going to meet her.

04:02.160 --> 04:05.560
We are going to have coffee.

04:05.560 --> 04:08.840
It is my cousin's idea.

04:08.840 --> 04:12.160
Marisa works with my cousin.

04:12.160 --> 04:14.680
I am not Marisa.

04:14.680 --> 04:17.680
Says Carla again.

04:17.680 --> 04:22.960
My cousin has a photo of Marisa, says the young man.

04:22.960 --> 04:24.920
She's tall.

04:24.920 --> 04:26.960
You're tall.

04:26.960 --> 04:30.480
Her hair is short and dark.

04:30.480 --> 04:34.320
Your hair is short and dark.

04:34.320 --> 04:38.040
In the photo, she has an Umbrella.

04:38.040 --> 04:43.120
It's a black Umbrella with yellow ducks.

04:43.120 --> 04:46.720
You have a black Umbrella with yellow ducks.

04:50.320 --> 04:54.360
Carla looks up at the old Umbrella.

04:54.360 --> 04:56.600
Marisa is a thief.

04:56.600 --> 04:57.840
She thinks.

04:57.840 --> 05:01.320
She has my new red Umbrella.

05:01.320 --> 05:05.280
Carla is angry again.

05:05.280 --> 05:10.640
Please don't be angry, says the young man.

05:10.640 --> 05:13.280
He looks at his watch.

05:13.280 --> 05:15.720
It's 3 o'clock.

05:15.720 --> 05:20.120
Marisa goes to work at 2.30.

05:20.120 --> 05:22.720
I can't meet her now.

05:22.720 --> 05:25.400
It's too late.

05:25.400 --> 05:28.520
He smiles at Carla.

05:28.520 --> 05:33.360
Let's have coffee together, he says.

05:33.360 --> 05:36.560
Carla thinks for a moment.

05:36.560 --> 05:37.640
OK.

05:37.640 --> 05:39.040
She says.

05:39.040 --> 05:42.360
Let's go to my aunt's cafe.

05:42.360 --> 05:45.320
The young man smiles again.

05:45.320 --> 05:50.080
That will be great, he says.

05:50.080 --> 05:53.000
My name is Paul.

05:53.000 --> 05:57.080
I'm a law student, third year.

05:57.080 --> 05:58.960
I'm Carla.

05:58.960 --> 06:01.040
I'm a student, too.

06:01.040 --> 06:02.320
I'm studying science.

06:02.320 --> 06:07.320
Carla sits in the cafe with Paul.

06:07.320 --> 06:10.320
They drink coffee.

06:10.320 --> 06:12.320
They talk.

06:12.320 --> 06:14.320
They laugh.

06:14.320 --> 06:18.320
They laugh and talk.

06:18.320 --> 06:22.320
Suddenly, Carla jumps up.

06:22.320 --> 06:24.320
Oh, no!

06:24.320 --> 06:25.320
She says.

06:25.320 --> 06:26.320
It's late.

06:26.320 --> 06:28.320
I must go home.

06:28.320 --> 06:30.320
I'm a study.

06:30.320 --> 06:35.320
I'm going to have an exam tomorrow.

06:35.320 --> 06:38.320
Good luck.

06:38.320 --> 06:40.320
Will you meet me again?

06:40.320 --> 06:41.320
Yes.

06:41.320 --> 06:45.320
That will be nice.

06:45.320 --> 06:48.320
It is almost dark.

06:48.320 --> 06:52.320
The town square is quiet.

06:52.320 --> 06:57.320
Carla sees a tall young woman.

06:57.320 --> 07:02.320
The young woman has short, dark hair.

07:02.320 --> 07:06.320
She has a smart umbrella.

07:06.320 --> 07:09.320
It is a red umbrella.

07:09.320 --> 07:14.320
The young woman is Marisa.

07:14.320 --> 07:20.320
Marisa sees the old black umbrella with yellow ducks.

07:20.320 --> 07:23.320
She is worried.

07:23.320 --> 07:27.320
Suddenly, her face is red.

07:27.320 --> 07:30.320
Don't worry, says Carla.

07:30.320 --> 07:32.320
Keep my red umbrella.

07:32.320 --> 07:35.320
I like this umbrella.

07:35.320 --> 07:37.320
It's a lucky umbrella.

07:37.320 --> 07:40.320
This is my lucky day.

07:40.320 --> 07:44.320
The rain falls on the umbrellas.

07:44.320 --> 07:46.320
Carla smiles.

07:46.320 --> 07:50.320
Then, she runs home.

07:53.320 --> 07:58.320
MUSIC

